e part where the device should be seen and there was nothing there. I am not sure if this was correctly executed though.\n\nI have another ATV (HD A1625 tvOS 18.4.1) that not used very much. So I went ahead and paired iSponsorBlockTV with YT there - it worked like a charm. I saw the notification in the YT app as soon as I started the container. \n\nSo it seems that the issue is with the ATV. It would be interesting to know if the other commenters also have a A2843. @t-hayash @lsanwick would you care to tell us on what device are you running the YT app?\n\n@dmunozv04 let me know how to send you that token/lounge ID. \nMy Apple TV is model A2843 running 18.4.1 [22L261]\nI have the same issue on my Apple TV. Have different models of Apple TV. Android TV and Vidaa (Hisense) works without any problems. Running docker image on Synology NAS\nThanks for your comments, I'll keep investigating but I'm unable to reproduce it currently on my devices. \nI've pushed a new branch that has http request tracing, so it can log all http requests and responses. It is `ghcr.io/dmunozv04/isponsorblocktv:http-tracing`\nEnabling the options `--debug --http-tracing` may log sensitive information, so you can send me logs via email: `<mygithubusername>@gmail.com` or via discord `@<mygithubusername>` (without <>). \nThis should hopefully help to understand what's happening and make debugging much easier. \nHey @dmunozv04 I just tested it and there is a big log but the most important part appears to be the one bellow. Just want to state that I am logged into my account, otherwise I couldn't even generate the token. Quite weird. \n```\n2025-05-22 20:29:23,657 - aiohttp_trace - DEBUG - Response chunk (0x14c10f2e1900) 280 bytes: <HTML>\n<HEAD>\n<TITLE>Connection denied. User most be logged in to cast to this device.</TITLE>\n</HEAD>\n<BODY BGCOLOR=\"#FFFFFF\" TEXT=\"#000000\">\n<!-- GSE Default Error -->\n<H1>Connection denied. User most be logged in to cast to this device.</H1>\n<H2>Error 401</H2>\n</BODY>\n</HTML>\n```\n\nLet me know if you wanna see the full log and I can email it to you.\nThanks for that @AN1MATEK! It looks very interesting. It would be great to have the full logs just in case they contain something else that may be useful\nEmail sent @dmunozv04 \ud83d\udc4d\nHi, just wanted to pop in that I'm experiencing the same (after months of happy sponsor-skipping)\n\nApple TV model A2843 running tvOS 18.5. I've tried (in various order) resetting the youtube app, clearing the config file and readding via TV code, and running the `http-tracing` tag with --debug mode. The logs indicate refreshed auth, and latest logs opening youtube and starting a video:\n\n```\n2025-05-24 17:48:35,833 - iSponsorBlockTV-7smtts7li1d6vhr61oomdm0gi6 - DEBUG - Waiting for device to be available\n2025-05-24 17:48:35,940 - iSponsorBlockTV-gn4h6m9l7u1u6et3l94v07ivtj - DEBUG - Waiting for device to be connected\n```\n\nRunning a very simple docker-compose.yaml:\n```\nservices:\n    iSponsorBlockTV:\n        image: ghcr.io/dmunozv04/isponsorblocktv\n        container_name: iSponsorBlockTV\n        restart: unless-stopped\n        volumes:\n       - ./data:/app/data \n```\nHi @hjdarnel, do your logs also show the `Connection denied` error? \nFor the http tracing flag to work, you have to set the image to `ghcr.io/dmunozv04/isponsorblocktv:http-tracing`\nHey, so I've been having the same issues for about a week as well (previously on v2.4.0, A2169 64GB, 18.4.1 [22L261], YT 4.50.03/web_20250521_15_RC00), and was silently debugging along with this thread. I updated the helm chart I'm using to v.2.5.0 yesterday and tried again -- no luck.\n\nToday however, suddenly, it started working again. No clue how/why. There was a `pyytlounge` error at some point however, after which everything became defunct again:\n\n```\n 2025-05-24 20:34:11,404 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Subscribe completed, status 200 OK\n 2025-05-24 20:34:11,545 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Connected to device None (AppleTV)\n 2025-05-24 20:34:11,547 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Subscribing to lounge id AGdO5p8pagVD7qcddv3-FhkGReKT071kPBapTznxc9PNmNhDdF-PLELplEEvtUOphbC4FVk-DtBy_2XkngtCKyNaJnuc695KOUDTCzXLfzLSZUzU-bfQ7VQ\n 2025-05-24 20:37:16,218 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Ad can be skipped, skipping\n 2025-05-24 20:37:16,220 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Getting segments for next video: jhrHL6s0NZs\n 2025-05-24 20:37:16,220 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Ad can be skipped, skipping\n 2025-05-24 20:37:16,325 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Ad has started, muting\n 2025-05-24 20:37:17,010 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Playing video jhrHL6s0NZs with 2 segments\n 2025-05-24 20:37:17,914 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Getting segments for next video: WHBLdBHmP-k\n 2025-05-24 20:37:18,124 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Ad has ended, unmuting\n 2025-05-24 20:37:18,127 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Playing video jhrHL6s0NZs with 2 segments\n 2025-05-24 20:37:18,643 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Getting segments for next video: EaCnovM9JSM\n 2025-05-24 20:37:18,849 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Ad has ended, unmuting\n 2025-05-24 20:37:18,851 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Playing video jhrHL6s0NZs with 2 segments\n 2025-05-24 20:38:33,655 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Skipping segment: seeking to 95.056\n 2025-05-24 20:38:33,761 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Subscribe completed, status 200 OK\n Exited\n Traceback (most recent call last):\n   File \"./main.py\", line 3, in <module>\n   File \"./iSponsorBlockTV/helpers.py\", line 214, in app_start\n   File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.13/site-packages/rich_click/rich_command.py\", line 378, in __call__\n   File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.13/site-packages/click/core.py\", line 1442, in __call__\n   File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.13/site-packages/rich_click/rich_command.py\", line 166, in main\n   File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.13/site-packages/click/core.py\", line 1808, in invoke\n   File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.13/site-packages/click/core.py\", line 1226, in invoke\n   File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.13/site-packages/click/core.py\", line 794, in invoke\n   File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.13/site-packages/click/decorators.py\", line 34, in new_func\n   File \"./iSponsorBlockTV/helpers.py\", line 166, in cli\n   File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.13/site-packages/click/core.py\", line 794, in invoke\n   File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.13/site-packages/click/decorators.py\", line 34, in new_func\n   File \"./iSponsorBlockTV/helpers.py\", line 192, in start\n   File \"./iSponsorBlockTV/main.py\", line 188, in main\n   File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.13/asyncio/runners.py\", line 195, in run\n     return runner.run(main)\n            ~~~~~~~~~~^^^^^^\n   File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.13/asyncio/runners.py\", line 118, in run\n     return self._loop.run_until_complete(task)\n            ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^^^^^^\n   File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.13/asyncio/base_events.py\", line 719, in run_until_complete\n     return future.result()\n            ~~~~~~~~~~~~~^^\n   File \"./iSponsorBlockTV/main.py\", line 174, in main_async\n   File \"./iSponsorBlockTV/main.py\", line 66, in loop\n   File \"/usr/local/lib/python3.13/site-packages/pyytlounge/wrapper.py\", line 81, in screen_name\n pyytlounge.exceptions.NotLinkedException: Not linked\n- isponsorblocktv-5c4d8575fb-rjmpt \u203a isponsorblocktv\n+ isponsorblocktv-5c4d8575fb-rjmpt \u203a isponsorblocktv\n 2025-05-24 20:38:35,944 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Refreshed auth, lounge id token AGdO5p9wUyFcAAZkpQJiCzFjqoJwdb_cuJ51ZSm3uG9-v0myZgA1erBkNyrG8Fw4UP36xAYbtuLPOmryOvL4fqOezx7bGpR3PxCtockGa0-aNwXSYOpr-Fw\n 2025-05-24 20:38:35,948 - iSponsorBlockTV-29fb0t98r7s1jito6frpmt1je6 - INFO - Refreshed auth, lounge id token AGdO5p9vZySqKa5ZWZ6vNhPEqNTGIfe-qKo6t1K2_jiNQhFTeScOzArhfsEccf63r1pPdAOQ3kaGjhOzJZ7iKHw3K8UqK0LANPIHC1HwwL8NMQCh55yf4LI\n 2025-05-24 20:38:35,950 - iSponsorBlockTV-98drooqejpahbnk140ub2658u8 - INFO - Refreshed auth, lounge id token AGdO5p-Bo1mQhH0iPuuDipHVdMWO3tPy9s6aeuHM7gs8gZbP5vccI6r80qTl19Aoqer5WIJ3KYY7Cdqa55C3Z0he_stTA_uUYp8E_zSE5W8Znxi8V5z-XCg\n 2025-05-24 20:38:35,953 - iSponsorBlockTV-rfvu209vatvg720emv1ch303o4 - INFO - Refreshed auth, lounge id token AGdO5p-qkhJZqw62FOhY80N6Jzc0rrQPhkG2BfdFnyPUd7xrukW8fXfKYNYDLOBAEL7wgx4O28he39rSlFpgJm3nQ54I59r0yKDhJxliGHtj31eMz2pdjfA\n 2025-05-24 20:38:35,954 - iSponsorBlockTV-1hkkkumm9j4dcar95377gral1o - INFO - Refreshed auth, lounge id token AGdO5p_hY5Yms6B_S2EW-r7TP-BNUpyTQI0TaicARj_N2RIZl-AO_x_I1GUEBpFzFMBAVruY889fiXLQ8rvn-KuwTpDnZec2aEB2nZ4I-R5GlEO-nCtv2Fs\n```\nDo note the IDs in these logs. I've removed the kubernetes Pod ID prefixing these `stern` logs for brevity, but you can see the container restarting after the error. After that, the ID keeps changing again, whereas it was the same ID before the error. Can't tell if this is significant.\n\nIf there's anything I can do to help collect additional data on the issue and/or do additional testing, please ask. YT is quite unusable without isbtv \ud83d\ude09 Many thanks for all your efforts!\n@dmunozv04 yes exactly, `Connection denied. User most be logged in to cast to this device`\n\n<details>\n<summary>Logs below</summary>\n\n```2025-05-25 05:26:17,397 - iSponsorBlockTV-7smtts7li1d6vhr61oomdm0gi6 - DEBUG - Waiting for device to be available\n2025-05-25 05:26:17,506 - aiohttp_trace - DEBUG - Request ended (0x7f5f673c3b50): 401\n2025-05-25 05:26:17,509 - aiohttp_trace - DEBUG - Response chunk (0x7f5f673c3b50) 280 bytes: <HTML>\n<HEAD>\n<TITLE>Connection denied. User most be logged in to cast to this device.</TITLE>\n</HEAD>\n<BODY BGCOLOR=\"#FFFFFF\" TEXT=\"#000000\">\n<!-- GSE Default Error -->\n<H1>Connection denied. User most be logged in to cast to this device.</H1>\n<H2>Error 401</H2>\n</BODY>\n</HTML>\n\n2025-05-25 05:26:17,509 - iSponsorBlockTV-gn4h6m9l7u1u6et3l94v07ivtj - DEBUG - Waiting for device to be connected\n2025-05-25 05:26:27,403 - aiohttp_trace - DEBUG - Request started (0x7f5f672599c0): POST https://www.youtube.com/api/lounge/pairing/get_screen_availability\n2025-05-25 05:26:27,443 - aiohttp_trace - DEBUG - Request ended (0x7f5f672599c0): 200\n2025-05-25 05:26:27,444 - aiohttp_trace - DEBUG - Response chunk (0x7f5f672599c0) 2 bytes: {}\n\n</details>\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Just updated to tvOS 18.5 but same issue.\n\nEdit: changing the container network type to host also did not help.\nHi there, would you mind removing the device from the config and pairing it again?\nI deleted the whole config file and tried again. Same issue unfortunately. Thank you for taking your time to help me.\n```\nroot@unraid:~/media/torrents# /usr/bin/docker run -it --rm --name='sponsorblock' --net='mgmt' -e TZ=\"Europe/Berlin\" -e HOST_OS=\"Unraid\" -e HOST_HOSTNAME=\"unraid\" -e HOST_CONTAINERNAME=\"sponsorblock\" --pids-limit 2048 -v '/mnt/user/appdata/sponsorblock/':'/app/data':rw -l net.unraid.docker.icon='https://github.com/ajayyy/SponsorBlock/raw/master/public/icons/LogoSponsorBlocker256px.png' -l net.unraid.docker.managed=dockerman 'ghcr.io/dmunozv04/isponsorblocktv:latest' --setup-cli\nCould not load config file\nBlank config file created\nWelcome to the iSponsorBlockTV cli setup wizard\nPaired with 0 Device(s). Add more? (y/N) y\nEnter pairing code (found in Settings - Link with TV code): 200904470370\nPairing...\nPaired device: YouTube on TV\nPaired with 1 Device(s). Add more? (y/N) n\nAPI key only needed for the channel whitelist function. Add it? (y/N) y\nGet youtube apikey here: https://developers.google.com/youtube/registering_an_application\nEnter your API key: [redacted]\nEnter skip categories (space or comma sepparated) Options: [sponsor, selfpromo, exclusive_access, interaction, poi_highlight, intro, outro, preview, filler, music_offtopic]:\nsponsor,selfpromo,exclusive_access,interaction,intro\nDo you want to whitelist any channels from being ad-blocked? (y/N) n\nDo you want to report skipped segments to sponsorblock. Only the segment UUID will be sent? (Y/n) y\nDo you want to mute native YouTube ads automatically? (y/N) y\nDo you want to skip native YouTube ads automatically? (y/N) y\nDo you want to enable autoplay? (Y/n) n\nConfig finished\nroot@unraid:~/media/torrents# /usr/bin/docker run -it --rm --name='sponsorblock' --net='mgmt' -e TZ=\"Europe/Berlin\" -e HOST_OS=\"Unraid\" -e HOST_HOSTNAME=\"unraid\" -e HOST_CONTAINERNAME=\"sponsorblock\" --pids-limit 2048 -v '/mnt/user/appdata/sponsorblock/':'/app/data':rw -l net.unraid.docker.icon='https://github.com/ajayyy/SponsorBlock/raw/master/public/icons/LogoSponsorBlocker256px.png' -l net.unraid.docker.managed=dockerman 'ghcr.io/dmunozv04/isponsorblocktv:latest' --debug\n2025-05-17 19:46:43,516 - asyncio - DEBUG - Using selector: EpollSelector\n2025-05-17 19:46:43,521 - iSponsorBlockTV-5nea16bfautufhd7qgrq4nfj2i - DEBUG - Refreshing auth\n2025-05-17 19:46:43,535 - asyncio - DEBUG - Get address info www.youtube.com:443, type=<SocketKind.SOCK_STREAM: 1>, flags=<AddressInfo.AI_ADDRCONFIG: 32>\n2025-05-17 19:46:43,565 - asyncio - DEBUG - Getting address info www.youtube.com:443, type=<SocketKind.SOCK_STREAM: 1>, flags=<AddressInfo.AI_ADDRCONFIG: 32> took 29.893ms: [(<AddressFamily.AF_INET: 2>, <SocketKind.SOCK_STREAM: 1>, 6, 'youtube-ui.l.google.com', ('142.250.186.78', 443)), (<AddressFamily.AF_INET: 2>, <SocketKind.SOCK_STREAM: 1>, 6, 'youtube-ui.l.google.com', ('142.250.186.142', 443)), (<AddressFamily.AF_INET: 2>, <SocketKind.SOCK_STREAM: 1>, 6, 'youtube-ui.l.google.com', ('142.250.185.238', 443)), (<AddressFamily.AF_INET: 2>, <SocketKind.SOCK_STREAM: 1>, 6, 'youtube-ui.l.g