BUG - Waiting for device to be connected\n```\n\nHey there @dmunozv04, I did some more testing!\n\nYT reseted, config.js too, then went to the pairing process and still having the same issue. This is my main ATV (4K A2843 tvOS 18.5 - issue was observed in 18.4.1 too). I tried to do LAN discovery but I can't really control the UI, even after pressing Ctrl+P. I got to the part where the device should be seen and there was nothing there. I am not sure if this was correctly executed though.\n\nI have another ATV (HD A1625 tvOS 18.4.1) that not used very much. So I went ahead and paired iSponsorBlockTV with YT there - it worked like a charm. I saw the notification in the YT app as soon as I started the container. \n\nSo it seems that the issue is with the ATV. It would be interesting to know if the other commenters also have a A2843. @t-hayash @lsanwick would you care to tell us on what device are you running the YT app?\n\n@dmunozv04 let me know how to send you that token/lounge ID. \nMy Apple TV is model A2843 running 18.4.1 [22L261]\nI have the same issue on my Apple TV. Have different models of Apple TV. Android TV and Vidaa (Hisense) works without any problems. Running docker image on Synology NAS\nThanks for your comments, I'll keep investigating but I'm unable to reproduce it currently on my devices. \nI've pushed a new branch that has http request tracing, so it can log all http requests and responses. It is `ghcr.io/dmunozv04/isponsorblocktv:http-tracing`\nEnabling the options `--debug --http-tracing` may log sensitive information, so you can send me logs via email: `<mygithubusername>@gmail.com` or via discord `@<mygithubusername>` (without <>). \nThis should hopefully help to understand what's happening and make debugging much easier. \nHey @dmunozv04 I just tested it and there is a big log but the most important part appears to be the one bellow. Just want to state that I am logged into my account, otherwise I couldn't even generate the token. Quite weird. \n```\n2025-05-22 20:29:23,657 - aiohttp_trace - DEBUG - Response chunk (0x14c10f2e1900) 280 bytes: <HTML>\n<HEAD>\n<TITLE>Connection denied. User most be logged in to cast to this device.</TITLE>\n</HEAD>\n<BODY BGCOLOR=\"#FFFFFF\" TEXT=\"#000000\">\n<!-- GSE Default Error -->\n<H1>Connection denied. User most be logged in to cast to this device.</H1>\n<H2>Error 401</H2>\n</BODY>\n</HTML>\n```\n\nLet me know if you wanna see the full log and I can email it to you.\nThanks for that @AN1MATEK! It looks very interesting. It would be great to have the full logs just in case they contain something else that may be useful\nEmail sent @dmunozv04 \ud83d\udc4d\nHi, just wanted to pop in that I'm experiencing the same (after months of happy sponsor-skipping)\n\nApple TV model A2843 running tvOS 18.5. I've tried (in various order) resetting the youtube app, clearing the config file and readding via TV code, and running the `http-tracing` tag with --debug mode. The logs indicate refreshed auth, and latest logs opening youtube and starting a video:\n\n```\n2025-05-24 17:48:35,833 - iSponsorBlockTV-7smtts7li1d6vhr61oomdm0gi6 - DEBUG - Waiting for device to be available\n2025-05-24 17:48:35,940 - iSponsorBlockTV-gn4h6m9l7u1u6et3l94v07ivtj - DEBUG - Waiting for device to be connected\n```\n\nRunning a very simple docker-compose.yaml:\n```\nservices:\n    iSponsorBlockTV:\n        image: ghcr.io/dmunozv04/isponsorblocktv\n        container_name: iSponsorBlockTV\n        restart: unless-stopped\n        volumes:\n       - ./data:/app/data \n```\nHi @hjdarnel, do your logs also show the `Connection denied` error? \nFor the http tracing flag to work, you have to set the image to `ghcr.io/dmunozv04/isponsorblocktv:http-tracing`\nHey, so I've been having the same issues for about a week as well (previously on v2.4.0, A2169 64GB, 18.4.1 [22L261], YT 4.50.03/web_20250521_15_RC00), and was silently debugging along with this thread. I updated the helm chart I'm using to v.2.5.0 yesterday and tried again -- no luck.\n\nToday however, suddenly, it started working again. No clue how/why. There was a `pyytlounge` error at some point however, after which everything became defunct again:\n\n```\n 2025-05-24 20:34:11,404 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Subscribe completed, status 200 OK\n 2025-05-24 20:34:11,545 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Connected to device None (AppleTV)\n 2025-05-24 20:34:11,547 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Subscribing to lounge id AGdO5p8pagVD7qcddv3-FhkGReKT071kPBapTznxc9PNmNhDdF-PLELplEEvtUOphbC4FVk-DtBy_2XkngtCKyNaJnuc695KOUDTCzXLfzLSZUzU-bfQ7VQ\n 2025-05-24 20:37:16,218 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Ad can be skipped, skipping\n 2025-05-24 20:37:16,220 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Getting segments for next video: jhrHL6s0NZs\n 2025-05-24 20:37:16,220 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Ad can be skipped, skipping\n 2025-05-24 20:37:16,325 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Ad has started, muting\n 2025-05-24 20:37:17,010 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Playing video jhrHL6s0NZs with 2 segments\n 2025-05-24 20:37:17,914 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Getting segments for next video: WHBLdBHmP-k\n 2025-05-24 20:37:18,124 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Ad has ended, unmuting\n 2025-05-24 20:37:18,127 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Playing video jhrHL6s0NZs with 2 segments\n 2025-05-24 20:37:18,643 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Getting segments for next video: EaCnovM9JSM\n 2025-05-24 20:37:18,849 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Ad has ended, unmuting\n 2025-05-24 20:37:18,851 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO - Playing video jhrHL6s0NZs with 2 segments\n 2025-05-24 20:38:33,655 - iSponsorBlockTV-p3kcfeq425r996b90njhiphoc4 - INFO 