ol object at 0x7faa093879d0>: SSL handshake took 22.8 ms\n2025-05-25 18:54:41,100 - asyncio - DEBUG - <asyncio.TransportSocket fd=6, family=2, type=1, proto=6, laddr=('172.24.0.2', 41262), raddr=('142.251.116.190', 443)> connected to None:None: (<asyncio.sslproto._SSLProtocolTransport object at 0x7faa08e66510>, <aiohttp.client_proto.ResponseHandler object at 0x7faa08e600b0>)\n2025-05-25 18:54:41,135 - aiohttp_trace - DEBUG - Request ended (0x7faa0918c0a0): 200\n2025-05-25 18:54:41,136 - iSponsorBlockTV-7smtts7li1d6vhr61oomdm0gi6 - DEBUG - process_event(onHasPreviousNextChanged, [{'hasPrevious': 'false', 'hasNext': 'false'}])\n2025-05-25 18:54:41,136 - iSponsorBlockTV-7smtts7li1d6vhr61oomdm0gi6 - DEBUG - Unprocessed event onHasPreviousNextChanged [{'hasPrevious': 'false', 'hasNext': 'false'}]\n2025-05-25 18:54:41,137 - iSponsorBlockTV-7smtts7li1d6vhr61oomdm0gi6 - DEBUG - process_event(onAutoplayModeChanged, [{'autoplayMode': 'DISABLED'}])\n2025-05-25 18:54:41,139 - iSponsorBlockTV-7smtts7li1d6vhr61oomdm0gi6 - DEBUG - Unprocessed event onAutoplayModeChanged [{'autoplayMode': 'DISABLED'}]\n2025-05-25 18:54:41,139 - iSponsorBlockTV-7smtts7li1d6vhr61oomdm0gi6 - DEBUG - process_event(loungeStatus, [{'queueId': 'RQGUlo4SPR29N6cDt9Tq0OLma-QJ0', 'devices': '[{\"app\":\"lb-v4\",\"capabilities\":\"dsp,mic,dpa,ntb,vsp,ads,pas,dcn,dcp,drq,isg,els,stcp,que,mus\",\"clientName\":\"tvhtml5\",\"experiments\":\"\",\"name\":\"YouTube on TV\",\"theme\":\"cl\",\"id\":\"60fbbfbf-f983-491f-baa8-26bf0e7148a5\",\"type\":\"LOUNGE_SCREEN\",\"hasCc\":\"true\",\"deviceInfo\":\"{\\\\\"brand\\\\\":\\\\\"Apple\\\\\",\\\\\"model\\\\\":\\\\\"AppleTV6-2\\\\\",\\\\\"year\\\\\":2017,\\\\\"os\\\\\":\\\\\"AppleTV\\\\\",\\\\\"osVersion\\\\\":\\\\\"18.5\\\\\",\\\\\"chipset\\\\\":\\\\\"AppleA10XFusion\\\\\",\\\\\"clientName\\\\\":\\\\\"TVHTML5\\\\\",\\\\\"dialAdditionalDataSupportLevel\\\\\":\\\\\"full\\\\\",\\\\\"mdxDialServerType\\\\\":\\\\\"MDX_DIAL_SERVER_TYPE_IN_APP\\\\\",\\\\\"hasIdentityDifferentFromCurrent\\\\\":false,\\\\\"switchableIdentitiesSuffix\\\\\":\\\\\"\\\\\"}\",\"receiverIdentityMatchStatus\":\"IS_RECEIVER\"},{\"app\":\"ytios-phone-20.15.1\",\"pairingType\":\"manual\",\"capabilities\":\"que,dsdtr,atp,vsp,mus\",\"clientName\":\"ios\",\"experiments\":\"\",\"name\":\"iSponsorBlockTV\",\"theme\":\"cl\",\"id\":\"f96dda85-6ea8-49a3-95f0-99ebb29185af\",\"type\":\"REMOTE_CONTROL\",\"localChannelEncryptionKey\":\"H2H32nhnyb0stgQOLAj3-4k5PDm_aYY-8_PNOkJMjH8\",\"receiverIdentityMatchStatus\":\"DOES_NOT_MATCH_RECEIVER\"}]'}])\n2025-05-25 18:54:41,140 - iSponsorBlockTV-7smtts7li1d6vhr61oomdm0gi6 - DEBUG - process_event(onPlaybackSpeedChanged, [{'playbackSpeed': '1'}])\n2025-05-25 18:54:41,143 - iSponsorBlockTV-7smtts7li1d6vhr61oomdm0gi6 - DEBUG - Unprocessed event onPlaybackSpeedChanged [{'playbackSpeed': '1'}]\n2025-05-25 18:54:41,143 - iSponsorBlockTV-7smtts7li1d6vhr61oomdm0gi6 - DEBUG - process_event(nowPlaying, [{'listId': 'RQGUlo4SPR29N6cDt9Tq0OLma-QJ0'}])\n2025-05-25 18:54:41,148 - aiohttp_trace - DEBUG - Request started (0x7faa091f2ce0): POST https://www.youtube.com/api/lounge/bc/bind?name=iSponsorBlockTV&loungeIdToken=<redact>&SID=9BBD4A944A5B555E&AID=9&gsessionid=rnbjWBb39riEetUGV-gYS9Dce3LeXudV33X7j_tuglo&device=REMOTE_CONTROL&app=ytios-phone-20.15.1&VER=8&v=2&RID=3\n```\n\n</details>\n\nWould anyone be willing to send me their screen id via email and give me a time at which the device will be on so I can further debug this issue?\n> Would anyone be willing to send me their screen id via email and give me a time at which the device will be on so I can further debug this issue?\n\nSure. Does it work right now? I think you have my ID from the last logs. Otherwise let me know and I will send it to you.\nAfter a debugging session with @hjdarnel (thanks!), there seems to be a way to bypass this error. Since the fix is semi-permanent (even a YouTube app reset keeps it working), I'd need confirmation from another person to make sure that the fix works properly when done automatically. \n\nI've updated `ghcr.io/dmunozv04/isponsorblocktv:fix-error-401-connect`. It _should_ be as simple as running iSponsorBlockTV, force closing the YouTube app on the screen when the logs tell you, and go back to normal. \n\nPlease do let me know if it works/doesn't work\n> After a debugging session with [@hjdarnel](https://github.com/hjdarnel) (thanks!), there seems to be a way to bypass this error. Since the fix is semi-permanent (even a YouTube app reset keeps it working), I'd need confirmation from another person to make sure that the fix works properly when done automatically.\n> \n> I've updated `ghcr.io/dmunozv04/isponsorblocktv:fix-error-401-connect`. It _should_ be as simple as running iSponsorBlockTV, force closing the YouTube app on the screen when the logs tell you, and go back to normal.\n> \n> Please do let me know if it works/doesn't work\n\nI will test this a little later this evening and report back!\nWorking for me now after changing to the fix-error-401-connect image.\nfix-error-401-connect image also works for A2843, but don't work for A1842 tvOS 18.5\nI can also confirm that it works! Great job David! The pop-up that a device connected is not there anymore, but that does not bother me at all.\nThat's awesome news! I'll be merging the fix and making a new release soon. Thanks again for your help debugging this\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/dmunozv04/iSponsorBlockTV/commit/166e238f417687a1601c386a292edc2e55d0dc21", "https://github.com/dmunozv04/iSponsorBlockTV/commit/fd6f0d7283a42b5d3152fdbccc35a8ec27f294a2", "https://github.com/dmunozv04/iSponsorBlockTV/commit/98c1211b0982b2697089b6f23d2a24d9000e3502", "https://github.com/dmunozv04/iSponsorBlockTV/commit/b5d275e01e4f01690a8d7b040070e120b4f6ef27"], "created_at": "2025-05-28T21:48:19Z"}
{"repo": "dmunozv04/iSponsorBlockTV", "pull_number": 405, "instance_id": "dmunozv04__iSponsorBlockTV-405", "issue_numbers": [403], "base_commit": "ba2dc35f05670360628a128111968308182a32c0", "patch": "diff --git a/src/iSponsorBlockTV/helpers.py b/src/iSponsorBlockTV/helpers.py\nindex 6a7adc6..2a1b4b4 100644\n--- a/src/iSponsorBlockTV/helpers.py\n+++ b/src/iSponsorBlockTV/helpers.py\n@@ -80,7 +80,9 @@ def __load(self):\n                     if i not in config_file_blacklist_keys:\n                         setattr(self, i, config[i])\n         except FileNotFoundError:\n-            print(\"Could not load config file\")\n+            print(\n+                f\"No config file found, using defaults. Config will be saved to {self.config_file}\"\n+            )\n             # Create data directory if it doesn't exist (if we're not running in docker)\n             if not os.path.exists(self.data_dir):\n                 if not os.getenv(\"iSPBTV_docker\"):\n@@ -174,7 +176,24 @@ def cli(ctx, data, debug, http_tracing, setup, setup_cli):\n def setup_command(ctx):\n     \"\"\"Setup the program graphically\"\"\"\n     config = Config(ctx.obj[\"data_dir\"])\n+    config_path = config.config_file\n+    before_mtime_ns = None\n+    try:\n+        before_mtime_ns = os.stat(config_path).st_mtime_ns\n+    except FileNotFoundError:\n+        pass\n     setup_wizard.main(config)\n+    after_mtime_ns = None\n+    try:\n+        after_mtime_ns = os.stat(config_path).st_mtime_ns\n+    except FileNotFoundError:\n+        pass\n+    if after_mtime_ns is None:\n+        print(f\"No config file was saved to {config_path}\")\n+    elif before_mtime_ns is None or after_mtime_ns != before_mtime_ns:\n+        print(f\"Config saved to {config_path}\")\n+    else:\n+        print(f\"Config unchanged at {config_path}\")\n     sys.exit()\n \n \ndiff --git a/src/iSponsorBlockTV/setup_wizard.py b/src/iSponsorBlockTV/setup_wizard.py\nindex 4e636c8..d4d5b53 100644\n--- a/src/iSponsorBlockTV/setup_wizard.py\n+++ b/src/iSponsorBlockTV/setup_wizard.py\n@@ -300,6 +300,10 @@ async def on_mount(self) -> None:\n         self.devices_discovered_dial = []\n         asyncio.create_task(self.task_discover_devices())\n \n+    async def on_unmount(self) -> None:\n+        if not self.web_session.closed:\n+            await self.web_session.close()\n+\n     async def task_discover_devices(self):\n         devices_found = await self.api_helper.discover_youtube_devices_dial()\n         try:\n@@ -387,8 +391,12 @@ class AddChannel(ModalWithClickExit):\n     def __init__(self, config, **kwargs) -> None:\n         super().__init__(**kwargs)\n         self.config = config\n-        web_session = aiohttp.ClientSession(trust_env=config.use_proxy)\n-        self.api_helper = api_helpers.ApiHelper(config, web_session)\n+        self.web_session = aiohttp.ClientSession(trust_env=config.use_proxy)\n+        self.api_helper = api_helpers.ApiHelper(config, self.web_session)\n+\n+    async def on_unmount(self) -> None:\n+        if not self.web_session.closed:\n+            await self.web_session.close()\n \n     def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:\n         with Container(id=\"add-channel-container\"):\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Setup prints misleading config error and logs unclosed aiohttp session\n**Describe the bug**\nSetup prints misleading config error and logs unclosed aiohttp session\n\n**To Reproduce**\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\n\n1. Ensure data dir exists but config.json does not.\n2. Run iSponsorBlockTV setup.\n3. Exit setup after creating config.\n4. Actual output:\n```\nCould not load config file\nBlank config file created\nAfter exit: asyncio - ERROR - Unclosed client session ...\n```\n\n<img width=\"538\" height=\"93\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/227d1bc1-379f-42ef-9ef0-dc10bce521a9\" />\n\nTo be clear, the config is properly generated.\n\n**Expected behavior**\n- No error message for normal first-run config creation.\n- No asyncio \u201cUnclosed client session\u201d error on setup exit.\n\n\n**Environment**\n\niSponsorBlockTV installed and run via systemd (data dir exists, e.g. /var/lib/isponsorblocktv)\nCommand: iSponsorBlockTV setup\n\n**Additional context**\n- Config.__load() prints error text for the expected first-run FileNotFoundError and prints \u201cBlank config file created\u201d even though it doesn\u2019t create a file (see src/iSponsorBlockTV/helpers.py (line 82) and src/iSponsorBlockTV/helpers.py (line 104)). This is misleading when the data dir already exists.\n- aiohttp.ClientSession instances created during setup are never closed, leading to the asyncio error:\n  - Setup wizard: AddDevice and AddChannel (src/iSponsorBlockTV/setup_wizard.py (line 234), src/iSponsorBlockTV/setup_wizard.py (line 387))\n  - CLI setup: src/iSponsorBlockTV/config_setup.main() (src/iSponsorBlockTV/config_setup.py (line 83))\n\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/dmunozv04/iSponsorBlockTV/commit/154bcce01fd6a5874075ebab1367bac4af27bc56", "https://github.com/dmunozv04/iSponsorBlockTV/commit/72013962b13499ef1a9b4712f3cd5b1de7b42043"], "created_at": "2026-01-26T03:14:42Z"}
{"repo": "dmunozv04/iSponsorBlockTV", "pull_number": 437, "instance_id": "dmunozv04__iSponsorBlockTV-437", "issue_numbers": [407], "base_commit": "a0c1ae1af5e33564a1df33dfa13162680ca15b10", "patch": "diff --git a/src/iSponsorBlockTV/api_helpers.py b/src/iSponsorBlockTV/api_helpers.py\nindex 33db3e9..e23bd90 100644\n--- a/src/iSponsorBlockTV/api_helpers.py\n+++ b/src/iSponsorBlockTV/api_helpers.py\n@@ -111,6 +111,8 @@ async def search_channels(self, channel):\n     @list_to_tuple  # Convert list to tuple so it can be used as a key in the cache\n     @AsyncConditionalTTL(time_to_live=300, maxsize=10)  # 5 minutes for non-locked segments\n     async def get_segments(self, vid_id):\n+        if not self.skip_categories:\n+            return ([], True)  # Categories explicitly empty, skip segment fetching\n         if await self.is_whitelisted(vid_id):\n             return (\n                 [],\ndiff --git a/src/iSponsorBlockTV/config_setup.py b/src/iSponsorBlockTV/config_setup.py\nindex fc19c23..c98b0b4 100644\n--- a/src/iSponsorBlockTV/config_setup.py\n+++ b/src/iSponsorBlockTV/config_setup.py\n@@ -120,7 +120,7 @@ def main(config, debug: bool) -> None:\n     config.apikey = apikey\r\n \r\n     skip_categories = config.skip_categories\r\n-    if skip_categories:\r\n+    if skip_categories is not None:\r\n         choice = get_yn_input(CHANGE_SKIP_CATEGORIES_PROMPT)\r\n         if choice == \"y\":\r\n             categories = input(ENTER_SKIP_CATEGORIES_PROMPT)\r\ndiff --git a/src/iSponsorBlockTV/helpers.py b/src/iSponsorBlockTV/helpers.py\nindex 2a1b4b4..16506bb 100644\n--- a/src/iSponsorBlockTV/helpers.py\n+++ b/src/iSponsorBlockTV/helpers.py\n@@ -36,7 +36,7 @@ def __init__(self, data_dir):\n \n         self.devices = []\n         self.apikey = \"\"\n-        self.skip_categories = []  # These are the categories on the config file\n+        self.skip_categories = None  # None = absent from config; [] = explicitly empty\n         self.channel_whitelist = []\n         self.skip_count_tracking = True\n         self.mute_ads = False\n@@ -68,7 +68,7 @@ def validate(self):\n         self.devices = [Device(i) for i in self.devices]\n         if not self.apikey and self.channel_whitelist:\n             raise ValueError(\"No youtube API key found and channel whitelist is not empty\")\n-        if not self.skip_categories:\n+        if self.skip_categories is None:\n             self.skip_categories = [\"sponsor\"]\n             print(\"No categories found, using default: sponsor\")\n \ndiff --git a/src/iSponsorBlockTV/setup_wizard.py b/src/iSponsorBlockTV/setup_wizard.py\nindex d4d5b53..e6c844a 100644\n--- a/src/iSponsorBlockTV/setup_wizard.py\n+++ b/src/iSponsorBlockTV/setup_wizard.py\n@@ -691,9 +691,10 @@ def compose(self) -> ComposeResult:\n         yield Label(\"Skip Categories\", classes=\"title\")\n         yield Label(\"Select the categories you want to skip\", classes=\"subtitle\")\n         skip_categories_parsed = []\n+        configured = self.config.skip_categories or []\n         for i in skip_categories:\n             name, value = i\n-            if value in self.config.skip_categories:\n+            if value in configured:\n                 skip_categories_parsed.append((name, value, True))\n             else:\n                 skip_categories_parsed.append((name, value, False))\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Skipping segments in video with no skip categories selected\n**Describe the bug**\nDespite having no skip categories selected iSponsorBlockTV is skipping in-video segments such as sponsorships.\n\n**To Reproduce**\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\n\n1. Setup config.json with no skip categories selected\n2. Enable skip ads\n3. Watch video on tv\n4. In-video sponsor segments still being skipped\n\n**Expected behavior**\nWith no skip categories selected only separate youtube ads should be skipped when possible.\n\n\n**iSponsorBlockTV server (please complete the following information):**\n\n- OS: Docker\n", "hints_text": "Hi there, this is a known issue that would be nice to fix. \n\nI'd like to work on this \u2014 will submit a PR shortly.\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Hi there, this is a known issue that would be nice to fix. \n\nI'd like to work on this \u2014 will submit a PR shortly.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/dmunozv04/iSponsorBlockTV/commit/bd4f438f7810e83d7ade82dcafa1728c35d8f906", "https://github.com/dmunozv04/iSponsorBlockTV/commit/8658cdbdc91f46217f6abbdda47372307c111463"], "created_at": "2026-04-08T18:49:17Z"}
